   "source": [
    "There are pillars near the road. The distance between the pillars is the same and the width of the pillars is the same. Your function accepts three arguments:\n",
    "\n",
    "number of pillars (â‰¥ 1);\n",
    "distance between pillars (10 - 30 meters);\n",
    "width of the pillar (10 - 50 centimeters).\n",
    "Calculate the distance between the first and the last pillar in centimeters (without the width of the first and last pillar)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "57efac56-a05c-4910-81ca-e8db0b72feee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def pillars(n, dist, width):\n",
    "    if n>1:\n",
    "        return (((n-2)*width)+(dist*100*(n-1)))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return 0"
   ]
  }
